        <intro>
            <p>
                Solve the following integrals. Note that there are many ways to write the same trig expression via identities.  Recall that <m>\displaystyle \sin^2(\theta) = \frac{1 - \cos(2\theta)}{2}, \cos^2(\theta) = \frac{1 + \cos(2\theta)}{2}</m>.
            </p>
            <!--<p>
                (If an open circle appears on an point which is not a jump discontinuity, ignore it.)
            </p>-->
